extends ../base

block content
  p Conversational copy is!{' '}
    span.italic writing how you talk.
  p No sales megaphone. No business speak.
  p But that's easier said than done. So I've put together this guide:
  h2.under 1/ Use contractions
  p Only academics say “you are”.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con1.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 2/ Load up on personal pronouns
  p People pay attention when!{' '}
    span.bold you
    |!{' '}talk directly to them.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con2.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 3/ Don't worry about grammar
  p If you break the rules you’ll sound human.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con3.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 4/ Ditch the thesaurus
  p You're not impressing anyone.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con4.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 5/ Start sentences with conjunctions
  p It's flows better.
  //- p It reflects how we talk.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con5.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 6/ Don't write AT the reader
  p Involve the reader in your copy.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con6.jpg" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 7/ Don't persuade
  p Let the reader!{' '}
    span.italic be persuaded
    | .
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con7.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  //- img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con7a.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 8/ Empathise
  p Understanding your customer is more important than impressing them.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con8.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
  h2.under 9) Respect the competition
  p It's reflects self confidence.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/con9.png" alt="Andie's CEO email").img__100
